The paper deals with Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs), which are typically studied in the areas of logic and discrete mathematics (cs.LO, cs.DM). The paper also draws on algebraic and topological techniques to characterize the borderline between hardness and tractability for a certain class of infinite domain CSPs, which suggests that it may be relevant to the areas of computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
